17 "(f) In the event that a local governing body acts in violation of this Code section, the
18 sovereign immunity of such local governing body and the governmental immunity of all
19 local officials and employees of such local governing body is waived in all matters arising
20 from or resulting in the violation of this Code section."
21 SECTION 2.
22 Article 1 of Chapter 4 of Title 42 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
23 general provisions regarding jails, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as
24 follows:
25 "42-4-17.
26 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'immigration detainer request' means a federal
27 government request to a local entity to maintain temporary custody of an alien, including
28 a United States Department of Homeland Security Form I-247 document or a similar
29 successor form.
30 (b) All sheriffs, jailers, and deputies who have custody of a person who is subject to an
31 immigration detainer request issued by the United States Immigration and Customs
32 Enforcement shall:
33 (1) Comply with, honor, and fulfill any request made in the immigration detainer request
34 provided by the United States Immigration and Customs Enforcement; and
35 (2) Inform the person identified in the immigration detainer request that the person is
36 being held pursuant to an immigration detainer request issued by the United States
37 Immigration and Customs Enforcement.
38 (c) A sheriff, jailer, or deputy shall not be required to perform a duty imposed by
39 subsection (b) of this Code section with respect to a person who has provided proof that he
40 or she is a citizen of the United States. Such proof may include:
41 (1) A driver's license or identification card issued pursuant to Chapter 5 of Title 40; or
42 (2) Government issued identification issued by the federal government or another state.
